provocarit (provocaverit): provocatio (appeal) was the technical term for the process by which a condemned person claimed a new hearing before the people in the Comitia Centuriam when found guilty by a jury-court. In the time of the monarchy all trials lay with the king and the quaestores parricidii, or perduellionis, the duumvirs here mentioned, and there could be no appeal except with the king’s permission.
